text: Cemal Gürsel (; 13 October 1895 – 14 September 1966) was a Turkish army officer. He was the fourth President of Turkey from 1960 until a few months before his death in 1966. He died from complications of a stroke in Ankara on 14 September 1966 at the age of 70. ==References== ==Other websites== *1963–1966 Landmarks of Turkish History * *Cemal Gursel's Memorandum Revealed *His video and photographs at the President's Web Page Category:1895 births Category:1966 deaths Category:Deaths from stroke Category:Presidents of Turkey Category:Prime ministers of Turkey Category:20th-century presidents of Turkey
